title: Vacancy
author: molly
text: an empty cardboard box filled with nothing but air a vacuum,  an unwritten writing,  a bowl of soup without the soup  a staff without any musical notes a bus lacking children to ride it a vacant hospital waiting room a grocery store with no groceries  a face that doesnâ’t have a smile a head without some hair no matter how much i look there will be nothing there.   my head is filled with vacancy,  like a calendar with no dates a schedule with nothing scheduled in it an unpracticed routine,  a pet store with no pets allowed for if vacancy exists,  it is really there  hypocritical,  you might call it,  if there were a house stuffed with vacancy,  then.  succinct,  a printer with no paper the printerâ’s filled with emptiness.   a vacant parking lot is a lot for parking with no parked cars nothing there,  you might swear cross your heart,  you may there will be much vacancy today.

author: morgan
text: leave me alone.  don't come any closer.  i'm so alone.  and you call me a loser.   he bitterest tears shed over graves are for words left unsaid and deeds left undone.   i cry for the time that you were almost mine,   i cry for the memories i've left behind,  i cry for the pain,  the lost,  the old the new,  i cry for the times i thought i had you      two shots of hate from a mouth as loud as a gun,  like an assasin . . .  who does it for fun.   two deafening blows in a war that has just begun,  life gone away. . . i'm am done.   two red roses sitting on my coffin,  the wind blows,  leaving only one the world i know disappears. . . like the setting sun.

title: Knights of the Right
author: n.

title: The Old Castle
author: n.
text: once before there stood a strong proud home,   that belonged to men and women alike.   they lived in its splendor and loved it deeply,   with the love of a people that enjoy life itself.    their castle soon could not stand any longer,   for guns and bombs destroyed its walls.   the occupants fled to safer homes,   and the castle was left to natureâ’s attacks.    here in this old forested place,   the castle stood proudly but weakly.   the aspects of nature destroyed the old castle,   until only its ruins were left.    only its remains were left in the old land,   as a sign that it once stood regally.   the old castle no longer physically stood,   but only stayed in our hearts and minds.    it only lives where people let it,   in hearts of imagination and love.   it only stays as a memorial of,   medieval times.

title: I Will Never let You Go.

title: My favorite place

title: I Am
author: natalia
text: i i am  i am natalia,  i wonder about the twinkling stars so high above my brunette head,  i hear sizzling bacon as i ferociously shake my head and disagree,  i see marching protesters holding up important messages,  i want an oinking,  whimpering piglet,  greeting me kindly,  i am natalia,  i pretend i am a scaly,  turquoise chameleon blending in with my floral surroundings,  i feel bubbly,  cheerful,  happy,  excitement,  i touch the smooth paper as i run my fingers over the many textures of words,  i worry that my family will not appear when i wake,  i cry about gossip and rumors swirling around.  the subject: me,   i am natalia,  i understand that people are suffering from problems i would never imagine having,  i say that nothing can break me,  i dream of being surrounded by adoring fans,  i try to never let my smile leave my face,  i hope that my positivity,  humor,  dreams and kindness will enlighten a depressed soul one day,  i am natalia.

title: My Tiger
author: nicole
text: my tigerâ’s scream pierces the night.  roaring and calling to me from afar.  his voice is all i hear tonight for i donâ’t understand him.  soon the light disappears and the darkness of night surrounds me.  now black and orange i can see no more.  alone at last  my tiger too.  i miss him dearly as should you.  his fur was soft as a cloud in the sky,  and his face sweet as sugar.   but the moon hung low and i couldnâ’t see him  on the night that my tiger died.  his glowing green eyes  caught me in a trace.  his eyes were beautiful and symbolized freedom.  but out of no where i heard his shrill cry.  knowing that his call  was sending me a warning.  i did nothing to acknowledge or help him help me.   he was running at the speed of light to stop what was approaching me.  the man with the gun stopped dead in his tracks still pointing it straight at me.  a shrill in the night,  and a splash of blood my tiger fell to the ground.  my tiger,  my tiger my tiger no more.

title: Love
author: nikkole
text: cherish love,  never let it fade.  a person without love is like a bike without wheels,  it just isn't right.  love makes you free,  wild,  and special.  i wish i would meet love soon. . . but i'm only twelve,  and i have a whole life to find it.  don't rush through your childhood,  is a lesson i have learned.  love is out there waiting for you,  so don't fret. . . . you shall meet it.

title: IT..........Bearer of Irresponsibility
author: nikkole
text: it rushes through my veins,  making me wild,  making me so amazingly free.  it makes me feel like i'm on top of the world,  and like i'm oblivious to anything but this extravagant rush of emotions.  it can sometimes get me into trouble,  yet i still smile and feel joyous.  it gives me the gift of absolutely no limitations.   what is it you ask? well,  it is caffeine.

title: Questions
author: nikkole
text: you used to be here,  but now you're nowhere near.  why did you leave? wasn't i your friend,  no matter what you did,  no matter what you said,  no matter what you felt? then why did you leave? why didn't you stay? i really miss you,  i really do.   why didn't you stay?

title: Rien Neala
author: nikkole
text: tis the safe haven for my soul,  a place of beauty,  free spirits,  and good will.  the angels of this place shall never let the dark seep through,  for they know how vulnerable my heart is.  i and other souls wander free from danger within this heaven's walls,  but if we stray from the gate even once,  we will be condemned to a life of torture.   this place,  this wonderful haven,  is a city of my imagination,  but through my writings and poems,  perhaps someday other curious hearts will come to believe in rien neala,  the safe havens for young imaginations,  too.

title: Why I Am a Stargazer
author: nikkole
text: the stars guide me through the night,  for they are my only light.  and as i cry for my lost love,  the stars comfort me from above.  those stars helped me through my darkest hour,  i am awed by their glowing power.  thank god for stars.

title: ~~~~My World~~~~
author: nikkole
text: i walk in a world of wonder and love,  where angels smile down at me from above.  i walk in a world where fairies dance,  and where you give our love one last chance.  i walk in a world where i can be free,  where i can be everything i want to be.   welcome to my world.

title: The Fruit of Hate
author: nikkole
text: the fruit of hate is bitter,  but yet we humans always take a bite.  we dare not taste the fruit of love,  for that fruit of hate is tempting,  blinding our sight to anything else.  the people of this world have all had their share of the fruit of hate.  oh how i wish for the time when the fruit of hate is gone,  and all that is left is love.

title: I Hate...
author: nikkole
text: i hate the way you stare,  like you will never care.  i hate the way you make me cry,  it feels like i'm gonna die.  i hate the way you point and sneer,  sometimes i just want to disappear.   i hate the way you hate me.

title: ~~~ The Chain of Friendship~~~
author: nikkole
text: friendship is like a gold chain.  it is pure and true.  but if the chain is broken,  it can be mended,  though the gold will forever be weak.

title: What is This Feeling?
author: nikkole
text: what is this feeling? it is dark,  cold,  exhilarating,  comforting,  unwanted.  it grips my heart with an iron fist,  unbearable and strange.  my pulse beats faster,  slower,  faster; my breath is taken by this feeling,   which holds me in a cage with no way out.  i try to escape. . .  i rattle the bars of the cage and plea for help.  but my efforts are useless,  my calls unheard.   what is this feeling? is it love,  is it hate,  is it fear,  is it sorrow? is it the dreadful anticipation os something to come? i shake my head sadly,  my heart lies confused and cries out in dismay.  i don't like this feeling,  and i wish it were gone.

title: Waiting for Love
author: nikkole
text: when will i find it? the thing i am so hopefully searching for; will i find it or will it find me? am i going to find it at all? i guess only time can tell.

title: Confusion
author: nikkole
text: boy,  you're one of my best friends,  and i love you with all the love my heart can give. . . but that love is the love of friendship.  now,  i'm starting to think you love me. . . with a different kind of love.  you look at me differently,  you stutter when you talk to me,  and you treat me with so much kindness,  that its getting kinda weird.  boy,  the last thing i want to do is hurt you,  but i'm afraid i don't love you the way you love me. . .   i hope our friendship lasts through all the obstacles life throws at us.

title: Love's True Form
author: nikkole
text: love's true form is a flower in a land of hate,  growing large and strong.  it can be a butterfly,  fluttering through this world freely.  maybe the form of love is a mother's tear,  as she sees her child for the first time.  or perhaps. . . love comes in all forms.  yes,  that's it.  love's true form,  is everything on this earth.

title: My Friends
author: nikkole
text: i have the greatest friends in the whole world.  they stick up for me,  they comfort me,  they act crazy with me.  i can always count on 'em,  no matter what.  sure,  we have fights.  but that just makes our friendship stronger.  sometimes one of my friends is down in the dumps.  but never fear,  nikkole is here,  to be as good a friend as they are.

title: Untitled
author: nikkole
text: as i think of your face,  my heart fills with love,  sorrow,  and longing.  you left me behind,  as you went from this world,  to the next.  oh,  i miss you so so much.  i miss the way you kissed my lips,  i miss the way you held me in your arms.  but you're always in my heart,  in my thoughts,  in my dreams.  i say your name to myself at night.  my tears poor like a great waterfall of sadness.  but the sun shines through my gusts of dejected love,  because i know that your watching over me,  and that your affectionate soul is constantly intertwining with mine.

title: Season of Hope
author: nikkole
text: this autumn is the season of hope.  hope for the world,  struggling to keep the fighting at bay.  hope for the united states,  who have tried so hard to keep terrorism away.  hope for for me,  who has just now begun to fit in. i now hope that peace for eternity,  will soon begin.

title: Complicated Friendships
author: nikkole
text: i used to have perfect friendships.  i had friends that cried with me,  laughed with me,  talked with me.  i had friends that were always there,  that never turned away to hide.  i had friends that i told my deepest,  darkest,  most secrective secrets of my young soul to.  i had the best friends in the world.   but now. . . o it tears me up inside to even think about it.  we fight,  we argue,  we lie,  we turn against each other.  we are divided.  we are divided because of the most ridiculous reasons.  boys.  decisions.  untruths.  and the cold,  actual truth.   o please god,  let us once more be joined in the bright circle of friendship. . . or else i don't think my poor heart would last.

title: Peace  VS. Hate
author: nikkole
text: why all this fighting? it doesn't make life exciting.  instead it makes life bitter and cruel.  life is supposed to be full of joy and meaning.  not pain and death.  let us make peace with ourselves and others,  and forever more be protected with the gift of happiness!

title: Reading
author: nikkole
text: reading is my way of gaining the cherished gift of imagination; it helps me grow in my mind and in my soul.  without books,  i wouldn't be the person i am today.  without books,  i wouldn't have the dream of writing novels,  and someday make a difference in the world of literature.   reading is my life.

title: I AM ME!
author: nikkole
text: i am me,   no matter what you think,  no matter what you say,  no matter what you do! i will always be me,  for eternity!!!

title: Thank you....
author: nikkole
text: thak you for noticing me,  for talking to me,  for listening to me.  thank you for holding me,  for loving me.   i thank you for these things,  for now and for always.

title: Why Does It Hurt?
author: nikkole
text: why does it hurt,  when you get scraped? why does it hurt,  when your heart brakes? why does it hurt,  when you hold all your feelings inside,  and never let them out? why does it hurt,  when you get hurt?

title: Happiness!
author: nikkole
text: happiness is such a simple thing,  yet some people say that,   they can't find happiness.   but that's impossible! happiness is always there! always right in front of you! always inside you.  happiness is always deep down in your heart. . . sleeping or awake.  now all you need to do if you cant find it,  is wake it up!! . . . see wasn't that easy? now nobody can ever say,  that they cant find,  wonderfully bright happiness!

title: ~~~~RAIN~~~~
author: nikkole
text: raindrops are like tiny crystals of hope,  falling from the sky above.   raindrops are like god's plentiful tears,  blessing us with the gift of life.   raindrops are like all the sorrows of the people of the world,  washing into one great storm.   raindrops are like my poems,  being shared by everyone and everything.

title: Where Are You?

title: Sweet Pea
author: phoebe
text: with fragile stem,  the sweet pea winds up slender trees grasping rough textures of the bark  tendrils like the golden locks of a porcelain doll exquisite foliage reaching out like little,  fairy fingers soft,  sensitive petals     with fair hues of baby pink and creamy white buds spring forth through the moist soil    like sunbeams peeking through dark clouds on a stormy morn with a subtle,  shy smile    the sweet pea gulps in the sunshine's rays miniscule drops of rain residue rest on the tender leaves aroma as sweet as the big,  blue eyes of a newborn child this is my sweet pea  it turns winter,  and my sweet pea's glow becomes dull its leaves change to brown then crinkle up  its once-long stem breaks,  surrenders,  and falls to the ground the petals shrivel and lean down their heads to the earth my sweet pea has died everything seem barren    except for the thought of next year's blossoms clenching the seeds in my hands,  i gaze out at the icy earth

title: Question

title: A Room
author: richard
text: i wake up in the morning to the warm rays of the sun.  the thought of school,  drives me back deep into the sheets.  as it has for years,   and years to come.  i couldnâ’t imagine,  a place i would want to stay.   i spy the colours of the fresh,  baby blue paint,  with the superhero stickers,  decorating the walls.  each colour,  represents a feeling,  a feeling of what it is like to be seven.  each is a memory of my past,  a reminder   my room,  my photo album,  the place where sweet pictures flood my brain.   the old clothes,  toys and books scatter upon the ground.  too precious to give away or throw out.  â“how do you sleep at night, â” some would ask.  â“with the toy soldiers at my side protecting me and my stuffies snuggling close to me. â” my room,  my wild kingdom,  the place where all my adventures begin,  and all my adventures end.   my room,  my peace and quiet.  i will have to leave soon,  to the outside world.  i will have to deal with the chaos outside yet i would like nothing more,  than to lie down and gaze out the window in my room.

title: The seasons
author: roguen
text: when the leaves turn red,  and the bears go to sleep,  i shall come home, to share with you,  the adventures of the keep.   in the winter when the trees are bare,  and the ground is white,  ill go away, until the spring,  to make sure the world is tight.   in the spring when the trees are in bloom and the bears start to stir,  ill be comin home,  to help you sir.   in the summer when the leaves are at peak,  and the bears start to explore,  ill be there,  to see you soar

title: State Fair
author: room 308
text: it's a cool night in november, perfect for fun.  me and my friends board the bus.  we laugh and giggle.  we're thinking about food,  rides,  and games.  in the distance we see the lights of the grand ferris wheel and we hear the hip hop music. . .  the sounds of people the bus stops,  the door opens,  and the fun begins!
